snippet.textDisplay:
So like I met this kid in school, I think third grade. I remember square dancing with him. We were friends, we would play on the playground and he would buy me ice cream. I gave him a grape soda pin. Anyway, he tried to take me to a middle school dance and his dad wouldn't drive him so he stood me up. I got really mad and stopped talking to him. But I didn't think we stopped being friends. I would still talk to him occasionally. High school ended and I went off to college. He started messaging me on Facebook asking me out on dates and stuff. He was nice to me. Really nice. my last relationship had been super abusive and it was just nice to have someone be nice to me. Anyway, I fell in love before I knew it. I was so happy to be with him. I would have married him if he wanted me to. A couple months later, he broke up with me. He couldn't give me a real reason. They all sounded like excuses. He kept kissing me and stuff too. It broke me into a million pieces.
A few weeks later, I notice my period is late. I start feeling really sick. I'm freaking the shit out. I don't know what the hell I'm going to do. I text him, Tell him we need to talk. He never responded. A week later I ask if he's just going to ignore me forever. He says "Yes." My heart breaks into a million pieces.

snippet.textDisplay: Okay in some of these stories, when the boyfriend forces his girlfriend into sex and then finds out she is pregnant, he just transfers schools or something immediately. But this girl’s boyfriend treated her right. By the looks of it and the way the story was told, everything seemed consensual. Even if it may not have been the best thing to do, at least nobody was raped. When he found out pregnancy was a possibility, instead of freaking out and ghosting her, he helped her and made sure everything was okay, even went to the doctor with her. I love how supportive her mother was as well, instead of grounding her and leaving her to fend for herself at the doctor’s, she helped and supported her daughter, regardless of whether or not she was upset with her. Overall, the people in this story were much nicer than people in other stories I’ve seen on this channel and similar ones (even though most copies are all fakes). I hope all is well with this girl and her family & friends. Sorry about the lengthy comment.
